Wash and dry produce.

Halve @ciabatta bread{1} crosswise; toast until golden in a #toaster{}.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @apple{1}. Cut @prosciutto{2%ounce} into strips lengthwise, then halve crosswise.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @arugula{2%ounce}, apple, prosciutto, half the @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Drizzle cut sides of toasted ciabatta with olive oil and halve on a diagonal.

Divide salad between bowls. Garnish with @pecans{1/2%ounce} and remaining feta. Drizzle with as much @balsamic glaze{5%teaspoon} as you like. Serve with olive oil toasts on the side.